* CSS - Cascading Style Sheets *

-> Ruleset:
    1) Selector
    2) Declaration Block
-> Declarations: script inside the braces

-> <style> -> goes inside the <head>

-> Examples:

    <style>

    p {
        color: blue;
    }

    </style>

* CSS Comments *

-> Comments are implemented by: /* */

* Tag Selectors *

-> Class : .class {}
-> ID : #site-description {}

-> An HTML Element can only have one ID, ID's can be used once!
-> Class order doesn't matter

-> Font Styles
    -> font-style
    -> text-decoration
    -> text-transform
    -> font-weight

* Developer Tools *

-> Chrome developer Tools:
    - CTRL+Shift+i
-> Browser specific developer tools

* CSS Units *

-> Absolute and Relative Units
-> Absolute: fixed values
-> Relative: relative to another property

-> Absolute Values:
    - Pixels
    - mm
    - cm 
    - in

-> Relative Values:
    - %
    - em 
    - vh
    - vw

* CSS & Color *

-> Color: byproduct of Red Green & Blue 
-> RGB Written as varying percentages of RGB
-> Color: rgb(255,255,255)
-> Hexidecimal: 00-FF
-> background-color: #ff00ff;
-> CSS Supports shorthand for colors!

* Border Properties *

-> None
-> Solid
-> Dashed
-> Dotted
-> Double
-> Groove
-> Ridge
-> Inset
-> Outset
-> Hidden

* Fonts *

-> font-family /* to specify the font family */

* Stylesheets *

-> <link href="path" rel="stylesheet">

* Styling Links *

-> Link Attributes:

    - a:link
    - a:visited
    - a:hover
    - a:active /* must come after hover */

* Height and Width *

-> Width: n px;
-> Width: n px;
-> Display Block -> to override default Properties
-> Min Height
-> Max Height
-> overflow: auto; /* Yields a scroll bar */
-> overflow: scroll;
-> overflow: hidden; /* Hides the overflow */

* Position *

-> Relative: elements site against one another
-> Absolute: top,bottom,left,right
-> Fixed: element remains in a fixed position in the viewport

* Centering a Container * 

-> Width, other than 100% is necessary
-> margin (is key)
-> margin: 0 0 0 0; /* TOP RIGHT BOTTOM LEFT */
    - margin-top
    - margin-bottom 
    - margin-left 
    - margin-right 
-> margin: auto /* automatically centers element */








